== Roasted Carrots & Broccoli ==

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat
#oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Trim, peel,
and cut @carrots{9%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Trim and
thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Toss broccoli on one side of a #baking sheet with a drizzle of oil, @salt{pinch},
and @pepper{}. Toss carrots on empty side with a drizzle of oil, a pinch of
@Korean chili flakes{1%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper.

> For 4 servings, spread broccoli out across entire sheet. Add carrots to a
> separate baking sheet; roast broccoli on top rack and carrots on middle rack.

Roast on top rack, tossing halfway through, until tender and crisp,
~{20-25%minutes}.

== Chicken ==

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels and season all over with
@garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, remaining chili flakes, salt, and pepper. Heat a
drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large #pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken;
cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> Swap in chicken for pork; cook until browned and cooked through,
> 3-5 minutes per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board. Wipe out pan and let cool slightly.

== Sweet Soy Glaze ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for chicken over medium-high heat. Add
scallion whites; cook until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon}
and @water{1/4%cup}; simmer until bubbling and slightly thickened,
~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from heat and stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} until melted.

> Use pan used for chicken here.

== Assembly ==

Slice chicken crosswise.

Add chicken to pan with sauce and toss to coat.

> Slice chicken crosswise and toss with sauce as instructed.

Divide carrots, broccoli, and glazed chicken between plates. Drizzle any
remaining sauce from pan over chicken. Garnish with scallion greens and serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.